World Bank Backs Economic Management Assistance
WASHINGTON , February 26 ( Xinhua ) -- The World Bank approved on Thursday a 15 million U.S. dollar loan for an economic management project in Thailand .
This project will provide technical assistance to improve the capacity of the Thai government for effective management of the country 's economy , which has been adversely affected by the recent currency and banking crisis .
The project will finance measures to upgrade macroeconomic management and public administration , reform public enterprises and strengthen the competitiveness of Thailand 's industrial sector .
The project is also designed to help contribute to a revival of economic growth and renewed export performance by bolstering the effectiveness of the public sector as well as the competitiveness of private industry .
